doc.after: Anabaptism is a Protestant denomination which originated in the Radical Reformation of the 16th century The term covers Mennonites Hutterites Amish and Brethren The Anabaptist movement started in January 1525 in Zurich Switzerland when the first Anabaptist baptismal service took place
